<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2022/04/twig-40/FwbIhWrhmzdcWxGIcRSSOAoc.png" alt="" />
</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>


<h3 id="furtherance">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#furtherance" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Furtherance <a href="https://github.com/lakoliu/Furtherance"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>Track your time without being tracked</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@rickykresslein:matrix.org">rickykresslein</a> says</p>
<blockquote>
<p><a href="https://github.com/lakoliu/Furtherance">Furtherance</a>, a time-tracking app for GNOME, version 1.1.2 was released with the ability to add tags! Some smaller improvements: the app icon is now aligned better, the start and delete buttons are now blue and red, respectively, and three more translations were added.

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2022/04/twig-40/WCAftxwNEEBkAVXhVpcEkYOx.png" alt="" />
</p>
</blockquote>


<h3 id="amberol">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#amberol" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Amberol <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/ebassi/amberol/"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>Plays music, and nothing else.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@ebassi:gnome.org">Emmanuele Bassi</a> says</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It&rsquo;s Friday, and there&rsquo;s a new release of Amberol, the music player with no delusions of grandeur! In this release I&rsquo;ve added a few niceties, like being able to see the position in waveform of the currently playing song; a remove button for modifying the playlist; and a whole new adaptive UI layout that works just as well on the desktop as it does on a mobile device. You can find Amberol 0.4.0 on <a href="https://flathub.org/apps/details/io.bassi.Amberol">Flathub</a>.

